As a die-hard player of the classical gem called System Shock, I find this Enhanced Edition somewhat meh, overall. My arguments below:
1. I was used to the old, classic interface and keyboard bindings. This mouselook stuff is ... well... clunky for me. I don't always remember to press E to switch between modes and it certainly hasn't become second nature for me;
2. Graphics are pretty polished. No arguing that. But it's a striking contrast between these polished tileset graphics and the original, already aged humanoid mutant; can't just look the other way with this one;
3. Music is MIDI. I get that. But playing the original floppy version on my old machine back in the day, I found the Sound Blaster music way better; maybe I'm biased, but since it's my review, it's my opinion, so it doesn't have to be objective ;)
4. The SHODAN graphics in the HUD telling you "it's blocked by SHODAN level security" are unusual and awful. They should have stuck with the original. Same goes for Rebecca Lansing's face. Wtf happened to that face? As an old player, this kinda breaks the experience for me. Not cool, Nightdive! Not cool at all.
5. I hear they put out a 4K resolution on their latest update. I find it useless;
6. Let's not forget (for those of you who know and remember) that this mouselook mod was a thing developed by some other guy on some other System Shock community forum/website (and it worked and behaved the same) before Nightdive released this Enhanced Edition.

All in all, if you want a refreshed (and somewhat fresh) experience in System Shock, buy it. But just don't expect miracles with this one. I enjoyed the hell out of the Classic version I bought a few years ago, remembering all that awe that made Shock a classic.

A message for Nightdive: IMHO, you should definitely stop updating this (IMHO useless) Enhanced Edition and give us loyal fans of the game that remake you promised over 2 years ago. 
A message for other players: By no means be influenced by my old-fart-rant-like review. It's simply my 2 cents on this enhanced edition. But at least it has a QUIT button in the main menu ;)
